theorem dense_of_denseInterior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior A) → Dense A := by
  intro hDenseInt
  -- `closure (interior A)` is the whole space
  have h_closure_int : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hDenseInt.closure_eq
  -- Monotonicity of `closure`
  have h_subset : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
  -- Hence `closure A` is also the whole space
  have h_closure : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x _; exact Set.mem_univ x
    · have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
        simpa [h_closure_int] using h_subset
      exact this
  simpa [Dense] using h_closure
